+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772766584715,"sessionID":"ses_33ee0aef8ffevSXsX8THlqnpyz","part":{"id":"prt_cc11f5c2f001fudS5orTkxsTNp","sessionID":"ses_33ee0aef8ffevSXsX8THlqnpyz","messageID":"msg_cc11f5705002jLS0CgS2x05SgD","type":"tool","callID":"8d8c1d2ae","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","content":"# Ralph Plan for In-Memory Task Queue System\n\n## Original Request\nBuild a fully-featured in-memory task queue system from scratch, progressing through 12 phases that incrementally add capabilities:\n1. Basic queue\n2. Named queues\n3. Priority handling\n4. Delayed tasks\n5. Retry with exponential backoff\n6. Dead-letter queue\n7. Task dependencies\n8. Concurrency control\n9. Progress tracking & cancellation\n10. Recurring (cron-like) tasks\n11. Middleware pipeline\n12. Graceful shutdown\n\nAll code must live under `src/`, exported via `src/index.ts`. No external runtime dependencies (dev deps are allowed). Write comprehensive tests, ensure `npm run build` and `npm run lint` pass.\n\n## User Clarifications\n- None provided yet.\n\n## Goal\nA TypeScript library implementing the described task queue with a clean public API, supporting all 12 phases, fully typed, thoroughly tested, lint‑free, and build‑able.\n\n## Approach (Phase‑by‑Phase)\n1. **Project scaffolding**: create `src/` directory, basic `src/index.ts` exporting a `TaskQueue` class with `add(task)` and `process()` methods. Define `Task` interface with `id`, `run(): Promise<any>`, and `status` enum.\n2. **Named queues**: introduce `QueueManager` that holds multiple `TaskQueue` instances keyed by name. Export `getQueue(name)`.\n3. **Priority**: extend `Task` with optional `priority` (number). Use a priority queue (binary heap) implementation in‑memory.\n4. **Delayed tasks**: add `delayMs` property; schedule via `setTimeout` or internal timer wheel.\n5. **Retry & backoff**: add `maxRetries`, `attempts`, `retryDelay` (exponential). On failure, re‑queue with increased delay.\n6. **Dead‑letter queue**: create a separate `deadLetterQueue` per queue; move tasks after exceeding retries.\n7. **Dependencies**: allow a task to specify `dependsOn: string[]` (ids). Queue checks dependency statuses before running.\n8. **Concurrency**: `TaskQueue` accepts `concurrency` limit; maintain a running count, only start new tasks when below limit.\n9. **Progress & cancellation**: expose `onProgress` callbacks, `cancel(taskId)` method, task status includes `Cancelled`.\n10. **Recurring tasks**: add `cron` string (e.g., `* * * * *`) using `node-cron`‑like logic (but implement minimal parser). Generate new task instances on schedule.\n11. **Middleware**: allow registration of middleware functions `(task, next) => Promise<void>` that can transform or abort tasks.\n12. **Graceful shutdown**: `shutdown()` stops accepting new tasks, waits for in‑flight tasks to finish or timeout, flushes state.\n\nEach phase will have its own unit tests in `test/`.\n\n## Key Files\n- `src/index.ts` – public exports.\n- `src/task.ts` – Task interface & status enum.\n- `src/queue.ts` – `TaskQueue` class implementation.\n- `src/manager.ts` – `QueueManager` for named queues.\n- `src/priority-heap.ts` – simple binary heap for priority handling.\n- `src/middleware.ts` – middleware registration & execution.\n- `test/` – Jest tests covering each phase.\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n- **Priority heap bugs**: write dedicated tests for ordering.\n- **Delay & retry timers**: ensure timers cleared on cancellation/shutdown.\n- **Dependency deadlocks**: detect circular dependencies and throw.\n- **Cron parsing**: implement minimal subset; avoid external libs.\n- **Memory leaks**: clean up completed/failed task references.\n- **TypeScript compile errors**: run `npm run build` after each phase.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Create project directory structure and initial files.\n2. Implement Phase 1 (basic queue) with a simple test.\n3. Update the task list status accordingly.\n","applyTo":"**"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772766584702,"end":1772766584714}}}}
